                                                                                                                       7                                      Rafi voted the best
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      
	New Delhi: Young striker Mohammed Rafi emerged as the Best Indian Footballer, while Okolie Odafe earned the distinction of being chosen as the Best Foreign Footballer for the second year in a row in the Lucozade Football Players Association of India (FPAI) awards, on Sunday.         
	In a glittering ceremony, attended by Asian Football Confederation (AFC) president Mohammed bin Hammam, AIFF president Praful Patel, sports minister M.S. Gill and host of other dignitaries, custodian Subrata Paul got the FAN Player award. While Joaquim Abranches was voted the Best Young Player, the Best Coach award went to Armando Colaco of Dempo. Anthony Pereira was named the Fittest Player.         
	National captain and FPAI president Bhaichung Bhutia was awarded for his contribution to Indian football. Arjuna Awardee Deepak Mondal and striker Sunil Chetri were also honoured.                                                                                                                     
